<p itemprop="description">A data ethicist ensures ethical and responsible use of data across the organisation. They provide guidance on data ethics, privacy regulations, and responsible data practices, helping teams navigate complex ethical considerations in data projects.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Assess ethical implications of data projects and provide guidance</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Develop and implement data ethics policies and frameworks</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Conduct privacy impact assessments and ethical reviews</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide training and guidance on data protection regulations</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Support teams in implementing ethical data practices</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Monitor compliance with data ethics standards and regulations</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Research emerging ethical issues in data science and AI</li>
    </ul>
</section>

